<TITLE> Metropolises to use electronic cash registers from Thursday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 31 (bdnews24.com)  Electronic cash registers will be introduced in the country's six metropolitan cities on the first day of the new year, NBR said on Wednesday. "District towns will have to use the device from July 1 next year," the National Board of Revenue said in a press statement. Hotels, restaurants, fast food shops, sweetmeat shops, furniture shops, beauty parlours, community centres, shopping centres, departmental stores, general stores, big and medium retail and wholesale traders in the city corporation areas must use ECRs for accounting procedures, the statement said. NBR chairman Abdul Majid told bdnews24.com. "The business community will be integrated into a modern accounting system through the introduction of the ECRs." "This will create a business-friendly partnership of confidence among the buyers, sellers and the government." Electronic cash registers will be applied everywhere in the country in phases, the NBR chief said. bdnew
